when I was 6, my sister was half my age. Now I am 80. How old is my sister now?
Your sister's age can be found by subtracting your current age (80) from the number of years that have passed since you were 6 years old. 
Let's call this time period "t". 
So, t = 2019 - 1974 = 45 
Your sister's age can be found by subtracting your current age (80) from 45: 
Your sister's age = 80 - 45 = 35 
Therefore, your sister is currently 35 years old.
